1
00:00:02,024 --> 00:00:03,072
剧情回顾...
Previously on Lost...

2
00:00:03,073 --> 00:00:05,024
我不在乎Jack怎么说
I don't care what Jack said.

3
00:00:05,025 --> 00:00:06,083
我们要把他救回来
They've got him. We have to get him back.

4
00:00:06,084 --> 00:00:08,038
我欠他的
I owe him that.

5
00:00:08,039 --> 00:00:10,039
那个屋子里的男人 你以前见过他?
The man in the house. You said you seen him before?

6
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:12,051
就是珍珠舱录像里的那个人
On the video feed from the pearl station.

7
00:00:12,052 --> 00:00:14,088
我们为什么还要兜圈子呢
Why are we continuing to play this little game,

8
00:00:14,089 --> 00:00:19,090
为什么不直接切入正题?
when we all know it has moved to the next stage?

9
00:00:21,068 --> 00:00:23,088
这张地图显示所有电能
This is a map showing electrical and data cabling

10
00:00:23,089 --> 00:00:25,086
提供给了一个住宅区
comprised of houses and dormitories.

11
00:00:25,087 --> 00:00:28,082
那地方一定很值得拜访
Sounds like a place well worth visiting.

12
00:00:28,083 --> 00:00:32,073
当我看见闪电击打顶棚时你被电死了
I saw a lightning hit the roof. You were electrocuted.

13
00:00:32,074 --> 00:00:34,028
你下水去救Claire的时候
And when you heard Claire was in the water,

14
00:00:34,029 --> 00:00:35,054
你自己却淹死了
you drown trying to save her.

15
00:00:35,055 --> 00:00:38,029
结果我下了水 你就得救了 我试过了 兄弟
I dove in myself so you never went in. I'm trying pal,

16
00:00:38,030 --> 00:00:41,091
我救了你两次 但不论我怎么做
I tried twice to save you, but no matter what I try to do...

17
00:00:41,092 --> 00:00:45,046
你都会死的 Charlie
you gonna die Charlie.

18
00:01:30,052 --> 00:01:41,082
妈妈? 妈妈!
Mom!

19
00:01:50,090 --> 00:01:57,006
看啊 Aron 你妈妈终于决定起床了
Oh look, Aaron! Your mom has finaly decided to wake up.

20
00:01:59,044 --> 00:02:04,095
多亏了我借走你的小矮人 你才睡着的
The only way I could get you to sleep in was to borrow the midget.

21
00:02:04,096 --> 00:02:07,017
这些都是什么?
And, what is all this?

22
00:02:07,018 --> 00:02:11,061
开味酒和这岛上神秘的水果
An aperitive, of mysterious island fruit.

23
00:02:11,062 --> 00:02:16,082
然后还有我特意为你准备的野餐
Before the breakfast picnic I have set up in your honor

24
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:19,008
就在不远的沙滩
a short walk down the beach.

25
00:02:19,009 --> 00:02:20,099
你怎么了Charlie?
What's gotten into you, Charlie?

26
00:02:21,084 --> 00:02:23,082
一个星期以来你都很沮丧
It's just, you've been so depressed all week,

27
00:02:23,083 --> 00:02:27,096
而现在 野餐和枕边小吃?
and now it's breakfast in bed and picnics?

28
00:02:27,097 --> 00:02:29,048
早晨醒来我想
I woke up this morning, and I thought,

29
00:02:29,049 --> 00:02:31,096
是时候振作精神了 让自己占有这一天
it's time to stop feeling sorry for yourself and seize the day,

30
00:02:31,097 --> 00:02:39,071
然后我就想到了你
and I can't think of anyone I'd rather do some day-seizing with than you.

31
00:02:39,072 --> 00:02:42,053
那...你怎么说?
So... What do you say?

32
00:02:42,054 --> 00:02:44,031
让我们把这小天使
Let's drop the cherub off

33
00:02:44,032 --> 00:02:47,059
交给Sun阿姨和Jin叔叔
with auntie Sun and uncle Jin,

34
00:02:47,060 --> 00:02:52,005
让我们去享受吧
and you and I go for a little stroll.

35
00:02:52,006 --> 00:02:55,010
正合我意
I would love to.

36
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:59,029
照小溪的方位 我们应该在这里
From the position of this stream, we should be here,

37
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:01,021
如果比例正确的话
and if the scale is right,

38
00:03:01,022 --> 00:03:05,083
他的人一定在那个方向的两英里外
his people are 2 miles in that direction.

39
00:03:05,084 --> 00:03:10,050
我没有期望你的确认
I don't expect you to confirm that.

40
00:03:12,012 --> 00:03:14,045
这只是电缆的地图 Sayid
It's an electrical wiring map, Sayid.

41
00:03:14,046 --> 00:03:16,007
我不像你那么确定它的精确度
I'm not sure it's as accurate as you think.

42
00:03:16,008 --> 00:03:19,035
那当然没有你那神奇的棍子来的精确
Well, it's certainly not as infallible as the magical carvings on your stick.

43
00:03:19,036 --> 00:03:21,064
那棍子带我们去了那个站
Hey, the stick didget us to that station.

44
00:03:21,065 --> 00:03:24,032
是那个你不小心炸掉的站吗?
Oh, the station which you accidentally blew up.

45
00:03:24,033 --> 00:03:27,012
如果你提醒我那到处是C-4的话
If you'd have warned me that the basement was rigged with C-4,

46
00:03:27,013 --> 00:03:32,013
我也许会小心点
I might've been a little more careful.

47
00:03:34,041 --> 00:03:37,051
你就不能告诉我们正确的方向吗?
Why don't you just tell us if we're going the right way?

48
00:03:37,052 --> 00:03:39,021
你们走的没错
You're going the right way.

49
00:03:39,022 --> 00:03:40,075
我们为什么让他活着呢?
Remind me why we're keeping him alive.

50
00:03:40,076 --> 00:03:42,057
你有什么建议 像打狗一样杀了他?
What do you suggest, we shoot him like a dog?

51
00:03:42,058 --> 00:03:44,070
不 我喜欢狗
No. I like dogs.

52
00:03:44,071 --> 00:03:48,032
他是对的 他们不会用他的生命和你的朋友交换的
He's right. They would not trade his life for your friend's.

53
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:49,037
我们应该杀了他
We should shoot him.

54
00:03:49,038 --> 00:03:52,042
够了 谁都别说了
Enough! Nobody's shooting anybody.

55
00:03:52,043 --> 00:03:55,023
地图告诉我们他们的方位他说我们的方向是正确的
The map says where they are, and he says the map is right,

56
00:03:55,024 --> 00:03:59,006
所以继续前进吧
so just keep moving.

57
00:04:03,061 --> 00:04:07,002
我们到了
Okay, here we are, here we are.

58
00:04:07,003 --> 00:04:08,010
不错是吧?
Not bad, eh?

59
00:04:08,011 --> 00:04:10,033
简直棒极了
Not bad at all.

60
00:04:10,034 --> 00:04:12,039
你先请坐吧
Well, if you'll take your seat,

61
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:18,094
我们有麦片 新鲜的水果沙拉
we will begin with our first course,which is cereal.We have fresh fruit salad

62
00:04:18,095 --> 00:04:21,061
早上好
Good morning.

63
00:04:21,069 --> 00:04:25,026
恩...早上好
Good morning yourself.

64
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:27,014
什么风把你吹来了 Desmond?
What brings you down to the beach?

65
00:04:27,015 --> 00:04:28,043
最近有许多野猪出没
Boar are running thick.

66
00:04:28,044 --> 00:04:33,035
我希望你和我一起去打猎
I was hoping you might want to join me on a hunt.

67
00:04:34,087 --> 00:04:35,099
谢谢你的邀请
Thanks for the invite,

68
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:40,085
但我们正在准备野餐
but as you can see, we're just about to begin a picnic.

69
00:04:40,086 --> 00:04:43,020
我认为打猎是一种...
Well, I think hunting might be a...

70
00:04:43,021 --> 00:04:46,010
很好的方式来消磨你的一天 Charlie
a better way to spend your day, Charlie.

71
00:04:46,011 --> 00:04:48,096
我的意思是所有的事中
I mean, of all the things you could choose to do today,

72
00:04:48,097 --> 00:04:50,099
打猎无疑是最佳选择
hunting with me might be your best option.

73
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,091
我的天啊
Oh, my God.

74
00:04:53,092 --> 00:04:54,098
怎么了?
What is it?

75
00:04:54,099 --> 00:04:59,087
我知道怎么离开这座岛了
I think I know how to get us off this island.

