78
00:05:25,097 --> 00:05:27,049
Sun! Jin!

79
00:05:27,050 --> 00:05:29,009
Claire 你怎么了?
Claire, what's the matter?

80
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:31,006
我需要Jin的网和鱼
I need Jin's nets and fish.

81
00:05:31,007 --> 00:05:34,033
我们要快点...还有水桶 我需要那个
We've gotta hurry. And buckets...I'm gonna need those, too.

82
00:05:34,063 --> 00:05:36,002
我们必须抓一只鸟
We have to catch the birds.

83
00:05:36,077 --> 00:05:38,070
他们刚飞过 而且就在这停留一天
They just flew over, and they're only gonna be here today,

84
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:40,059
所以要捉的话 只有今天
so to catch one, we need to do it now.

85
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:43,034
那听起来很有趣
Oh, this sounds like fun.

86
00:05:43,035 --> 00:05:44,048
你能弄些网来吗?
Can you get some nets?

87
00:05:44,049 --> 00:05:49,047
网用来干嘛Barb...
Nets for what, Barb...

88
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:51,089
网用来干嘛 Claire?
Nets for what, Claire?

89
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:55,079
5分钟前 一群海鸟飞过我的头顶
Okay, five minutes ago, a flock of sea birds flew over my head.

90
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,098
海鸟会迁移
Seabirds are migratory,

91
00:05:56,099 --> 00:06:00,028
他们会继续向南飞
which means they're gonna keep heading south.

92
00:06:00,029 --> 00:06:02,019
抱歉 我还是不明白
I'm sorry. I don't understand why we need to...

93
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:03,048
他们被挂了标签
They're tagged.

94
00:06:03,049 --> 00:06:05,011
标签?
Tagged?

95
00:06:05,012 --> 00:06:07,058
科学家给他们做了标签 为了追踪研究他们
Scientists tag these birds so they can track them.

96
00:06:07,059 --> 00:06:11,098
如果他们到了澳大利亚或新西兰
So when they eventually land in Australia or New Zealand or wherever,

97
00:06:11,099 --> 00:06:15,047
有人会收集他们的
somebody's gonna gather them up.

98
00:06:15,048 --> 00:06:17,014
如果我们捉住一只
We can send a message.

99
00:06:17,015 --> 00:06:18,045
我们可以靠他们传递消息
If we can catch one.

100
00:06:18,046 --> 00:06:19,045
好了 这是我们的计划
Okay, so here's the plan.

101
00:06:19,046 --> 00:06:21,039
首先把鱼弄碎
First, we've gotta cut up these fish, make chum.

102
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,036
鸟儿会来觅食的
That'll get the birds to settle in the water.

103
00:06:23,037 --> 00:06:26,058
我们要重新布置网
And then, um, we're gonna need to cut up some of this net.

104
00:06:26,059 --> 00:06:30,028
Charlie能把刀递给我吗?
Charlie, can you go get some knives?

105
00:06:30,058 --> 00:06:33,021
Charlie

106
00:06:33,022 --> 00:06:34,038
Charlie!

107
00:06:34,039 --> 00:06:36,082
是的
Yeah.

108
00:06:36,083 --> 00:06:39,055
你是怎么知道这些的 Claire?
How do you even know this stuff about birds?

109
00:06:39,056 --> 00:06:42,036
那是因为我和妈妈看太多自然节目了
I watched a lot of nature shows with my mum.

110
00:06:42,037 --> 00:06:45,072
那也不能让你成为专家啊
Doesn't exactly make you an expert.

111
00:06:45,073 --> 00:06:46,055
我只是...
I just...

112
00:06:46,056 --> 00:06:52,036
我只是不想让你浪费时间罢了
I don't want to see you wasting your time, that's all.

113
00:06:52,037 --> 00:06:57,002
你不是说好"占有"这一天的吗?
So what happened to seizing the day?

114
00:06:57,061 --> 00:06:59,097
抱歉
Sorry.

115
00:06:59,098 --> 00:07:04,043
是我没发现这一点
Don't see the point.

116
00:07:14,062 --> 00:07:15,069
稳住了 亲爱的
Hold still, dear.

117
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:18,038
马上就好
Just another second.

118
00:07:18,039 --> 00:07:20,020
行了
There.

119
00:07:20,021 --> 00:07:23,008
没事了
We're through now.

120
00:07:26,095 --> 00:07:29,003
Littleton女士 我是Barnes警官
Ms. Littleton, I'm Officer Barnes.

121
00:07:29,004 --> 00:07:31,089
很抱歉打扰您 但我需要问几个问题
Sorry to bother you, but I need to ask you a few questions.

122
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:36,035
事故是怎么发生的?
Can I ask you how the accident happened?

123
00:07:36,036 --> 00:07:39,037
一辆卡车把我们撞出路面
A truck forced us off the road.

124
00:07:39,038 --> 00:07:45,018
谁在驾驶?
Okay, and who was driving?

125
00:07:45,019 --> 00:07:48,075
我
Me.

126
00:07:48,076 --> 00:07:50,040
有人联系你父亲吗?
Has anyone contacted your father?

127
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:52,026
我2岁时父亲就去世了
My father died when I was 2.

128
00:07:52,027 --> 00:07:55,078
很抱歉
Sorry to hear that.

129
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:57,041
我和卡车司机谈过
I spoke with the truck driver.

130
00:07:57,042 --> 00:07:58,076
他很好
He's fine, by the way.

131
00:07:58,077 --> 00:08:00,037
他说你撞了他...
He said that when you hit him...

132
00:08:00,038 --> 00:08:02,055
不 是他撞的我们
No, he hit us.

133
00:08:02,056 --> 00:08:05,053
事故发生时你的车速是多少?
About what speed would you say that happened when you were driving?

134
00:08:05,054 --> 00:08:07,060
他突然就冒了出来 我没有...
It just came out of nowhere.

135
00:08:07,061 --> 00:08:11,017
你没有回答我的问题 Littleton女士
That's not the question I asked, Ms. Littleton.

136
00:08:11,018 --> 00:08:15,033
我不知道当时的车速
I don't know how fast I was driving.

137
00:08:15,034 --> 00:08:18,031
你为什么要问这些问题?
Why are you even asking me these questions?

138
00:08:18,032 --> 00:08:23,016
抱歉这是程序
These questions are standard procedure when there's a fatality.

139
00:08:23,017 --> 00:08:25,071
我母亲在开刀
My mother is in surgery.

140
00:08:25,072 --> 00:08:27,055
她还没死
She's not dead.

141
00:08:27,056 --> 00:08:30,079
是啊
Right.

142
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,076
那就是了
So she is.

143
00:08:31,077 --> 00:08:36,002
这不是我的错
You know, this is not my fault!

144
00:08:36,003 --> 00:08:37,068
我没有说是你的错
Didn't say it was.

145
00:08:37,069 --> 00:08:41,032
祝你有愉快的一天 Littleton女士
Good day, Ms. Littleton.

146
00:08:53,050 --> 00:08:57,079
能问你个问题吗?
Can I ask you something?

147
00:09:07,044 --> 00:09:12,072
我告诉你你女儿和他们在一起...
I told you that your daughter was living with them...

148
00:09:12,073 --> 00:09:15,040
而你竟然没问我一个问题
and you haven't asked me a single question about her.

149
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,033
你没有...
You haven't...

150
00:09:16,034 --> 00:09:19,082
你的朋友 Jack
Your friend Jack,

151
00:09:19,083 --> 00:09:23,074
你关切他吗?
you care about him?

152
00:09:23,075 --> 00:09:26,011
是的
Yes.

153
00:09:26,012 --> 00:09:28,064
设想一下16年后
Imagine 16 years from now,

154
00:09:28,065 --> 00:09:30,094
你被告知他还活着
you're told he's still alive.

155
00:09:30,095 --> 00:09:32,056
然而你告诉自己
But in your heart,

156
00:09:32,057 --> 00:09:36,007
他可能甚至都不记得你了
you know that he wouldn't remember you.

157
00:09:36,008 --> 00:09:39,023
他根本不认识你了
He wouldn't know you.

158
00:09:39,024 --> 00:09:40,087
那还会了解
Wouldn't even know

159
00:09:40,088 --> 00:09:47,009
你关切过他吗?
that you ever cared about him.

160
00:09:51,075 --> 00:09:56,036
我没有问你我女儿的事...
I haven't asked you questions about my daughter...

161
00:09:56,037 --> 00:10:02,018
因为我不想知道答案
because I do not want to know the answers.

162
00:10:15,075 --> 00:10:17,028
水?
Water?

163
00:10:17,029 --> 00:10:20,037
不了 谢谢
No, thank you.

164
00:10:20,038 --> 00:10:22,021
你是怎么来这里的?
So how'd you get here?

165
00:10:22,022 --> 00:10:23,077
怎么来到这座岛上的?
How'd you get onto this island?

166
00:10:23,078 --> 00:10:27,051
不要浪费口舌了 他说的都不是真话
Don't waste your breath. Whatever he says will be a lie.

167
00:10:27,052 --> 00:10:29,085
24岁是我被招入了新兵
I was recruited when I was 24.

168
00:10:29,086 --> 00:10:30,091
有一个人和我接触...
I was approached by a man...

169
00:10:30,092 --> 00:10:33,065
我没有问什么时候 我问你是怎么来的
I didn't ask you when I asked you how.

170
00:10:33,066 --> 00:10:35,091
坐潜水艇来的
They brought me on the submarine.

171
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:38,078
你们的人...他们能随意进出?
So your people, they can just come and go whenever they want?

172
00:10:38,079 --> 00:10:41,011
去 是的 可两星期以前
Go, yes, but two weeks ago,

173
00:10:41,012 --> 00:10:44,099
海底灯标停止接收信号
our underwater beacon stopped emitting its locator signal.

174
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:48,059
出了事故...是电磁回路
There was an event...an electromagnetic pulse.

175
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:50,030
回来就不可能了
It would be impossible to come back.

176
00:10:50,031 --> 00:10:51,065
你为什么想回来?
Why would you want to come back?

177
00:10:51,066 --> 00:10:56,089
你不会明白的
You would not understand.

178
00:10:56,090 --> 00:10:58,078
说来听听
Try me.

179
00:10:58,079 --> 00:11:00,068
我不会说的
I misspoke.

180
00:11:00,069 --> 00:11:02,063
我想说的是
What I meant to say is,

181
00:11:02,064 --> 00:11:04,019
你没有理解的能力
you're not capable of understanding.

182
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:05,066
那又是为什么呢?
And why am I not capable?

183
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:07,034
Kate

184
00:11:07,035 --> 00:11:11,068
因为你不在名单上
Because you are not on the list.

185
00:11:11,069 --> 00:11:16,013
什么名单?
What list?

