he is... a magnificent man.

189
00:11:26,096 --> 00:11:30,041
如果Ben很伟大 那为什么需要我们中的一个人来救他呢?
If Ben's so magnificent, then why did he need one of us to save him?

190
00:11:30,042 --> 00:11:35,075
Ben? Ben不是...
Ben? Ben is not...

191
00:11:35,076 --> 00:11:38,076
简单点说
I will try to make this as simple as I can.

192
00:11:38,077 --> 00:11:43,059
你们不在名单里 因为你们有瑕疵
You are not on the list because you are flawed

193
00:11:43,060 --> 00:11:47,000
因为你们愤怒
Because you are angry

194
00:11:47,001 --> 00:11:50,069
虚弱 恐惧
And weak and frightened.

195
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:52,026
越了解你们的人
The more I learn about your people,

196
00:11:52,027 --> 00:11:56,055
我就越怀疑 你们是不是真的无所不知
the more I suspect you're not as omniscient as you'd have us believe.

197
00:11:56,056 --> 00:11:58,089
别装作你很了解我们
Don't speak to us as if you know us.

198
00:11:58,090 --> 00:12:01,074
我当然不了解你 Sayid Jarrah
Of course I don't know you, Sayid Jarrah.

199
00:12:01,075 --> 00:12:04,060
我怎么会呢?
How could I?

200
00:12:04,061 --> 00:12:10,058
Kate Austen 你对我来说就是个陌生人
And you, Kate Austen, are a complete stranger to me.

201
00:12:10,059 --> 00:12:14,095
但John Locke 你...我想起来...
But you, John Locke, you, I might have a fleeting memory of,

202
00:12:14,096 --> 00:12:16,040
我一定是糊涂了
but I must be confused,

203
00:12:16,041 --> 00:12:21,007
因为我认识的John Locke曾是...
because the John Locke I know was para...

204
00:12:21,008 --> 00:12:25,019
来看看这个
Look at this.

205
00:12:28,056 --> 00:12:33,024
在这边 快点
Over here. Come on.

206
00:13:15,054 --> 00:13:20,009
看来我们到了
Well, looks like we're here.

207
00:13:24,091 --> 00:13:25,089
这能行吗?
Will this work?

208
00:13:25,090 --> 00:13:30,027
是的 能行
Yes. Work.

209
00:13:37,032 --> 00:13:40,084
能帮一下Sun的忙吗
Sun Please... Help.

210
00:13:40,085 --> 00:13:44,005
好的
Ok.

211
00:13:49,098 --> 00:13:51,072
真难闻啊
Smells great.

212
00:13:51,073 --> 00:13:57,018
我们来处理吧
Let's get it over with.

213
00:13:57,019 --> 00:13:59,077
我妈妈最怕这个了
This was my mother's worst fear.

214
00:13:59,078 --> 00:14:00,083
什么意思?
What do you mean?

215
00:14:00,084 --> 00:14:03,051
最后我就干这个
That I would end up doing something very much like this,

216
00:14:03,052 --> 00:14:08,007
做诱饵 她对我的期望值很高
cutting bait. She had high hopes for my future.

217
00:14:08,008 --> 00:14:13,006
他们也没想到我会嫁给渔夫的儿子
They did not include me marrying a fisherman's son.

218
00:14:13,007 --> 00:14:16,061
看来我们都不能实现母亲的愿望了
Well, I guess we don't always turn out like our mothers want.

219
00:14:16,062 --> 00:14:22,090
当然 我妈妈从来不做事
Of course, mine never worked a day in her life.

220
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:28,030
我妈妈曾是个图书管理员
My mom was a librarian.

221
00:14:28,031 --> 00:14:33,071
曾是?
Was?

222
00:14:36,003 --> 00:14:40,090
我们该干活了
We should get this stuff out there.

223
00:15:00,064 --> 00:15:04,082
你去哪儿了?
Where were you?

224
00:15:04,083 --> 00:15:07,040
回家洗了个澡
I went home to take a shower.

225
00:15:07,041 --> 00:15:08,093
那一定很舒服
That must have been nice.

226
00:15:08,094 --> 00:15:13,060
他们说她还在手术中
They said she was still in surgery.

227
00:15:13,061 --> 00:15:16,018
我也受伤了 Lindsey姑妈
I had glass in my hair, Aunt Lindsey.

228
00:15:16,019 --> 00:15:23,062
我很高兴你恢复精神了
Well, I'm glad that you're feeling refreshed.

229
00:15:23,085 --> 00:15:28,012
下午好 你是她女儿吗?
Good afternoon. Are you the daughter?

230
00:15:28,013 --> 00:15:30,067
我是Woodrufffrom医生 神经科的
I'm Dr. Woodruff from neurosurgery.

231
00:15:30,068 --> 00:15:32,048
她还要接受几天的观察
I'll be observing your mother for the next few days.

232
00:15:32,049 --> 00:15:34,032
她怎么样?
How is she?

233
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:38,044
